There was variation in the percentage of positive samples detected by each assay. The RT-iiPCR assay detected the most, while EM detected the least. The overall percentages of positive samples by each diagnostic assay are shown in Table 2
. There was a significant difference in the number of positive samples detected with the in-house rtRT-PCR assay versus the other two molecular tests. These differences are evident when comparing the Kappa coefficients (Table 3
).
